/*
Challenge 9: Sort Numbers in Ascending Order
Skills[arrays][numbers][sorting]

Create a method that takes an array of integers and returns a new array, sorted in ascending order (smallest to biggest).
Rules
Sort integer array in ascending order.
If functions argument is an empty array, return an empty array.
Return new array of sorted integers.
Examples
[1, 2, 10, 50, 5] ➞ [1, 2, 5, 10, 50]

[80, 29, 4, -95, -24, 85] ➞ [-95, -24, 4, 29, 80, 85]

null ➞ []

[] ➞ []
Notes
The numbers being passed to sortNumsAscending() can be positive or negative.


*/

    public static int[] sortAscending(int[] nums) {
        // we start with our null array statement
        if (nums.length == 0) {  // if array length is null
            System.out.println(Arrays.toString(nums) + "The string is empty"); // turn array to string and test
            return nums; // return []
        } else {
            Arrays.sort(nums);  // else we sort array in ascending order
            System.out.println(Arrays.toString(nums)); // test
            return nums; // return the sorted int array!
        }

    }
